00:13:34,320 --> 00:13:37,120
I thought the alarm clock was ringing

261
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:38,920
but I couldn't stop it.

262
00:13:38,920 --> 00:13:42,320
I heard somebody say, "Somebody fell!" before I went to the john,

263
00:13:42,320 --> 00:13:45,920
and was concerned, but I couldn't hold it any longer.

264
00:13:45,920 --> 00:13:49,020
And, you mean the alarm had stopped after you came out of the restroom

265
00:13:49,020 --> 00:13:51,520
and headed for the site then?

266
00:13:51,520 --> 00:13:55,120
Yes. After watching soccer for a while though.

267
00:13:55,120 --> 00:13:58,420
Darn, his story's consistent.

268
00:13:58,420 --> 00:14:02,020
And besides, didn't you say, officer...

269
00:14:02,020 --> 00:14:03,420
If I were the culprit, used the stairs,

270
00:14:03,420 --> 00:14:07,720
went up 23 floors to the president's room to push him off,

271
00:14:07,720 --> 00:14:10,120
and ran down the stairs to the first floor.

272
00:14:10,120 --> 00:14:12,120
It would mean that my room would've been empty

273
00:14:12,120 --> 00:14:15,620
for more than 10 minutes until you came to my room.

274
00:14:15,620 --> 00:14:16,920
The foam of the beer would've been gone,

275
00:14:16,920 --> 00:14:20,520
like that beer, if left as is for 10 minutes.

276
00:14:21,720 --> 00:14:24,420
But when you came to my room, officer,

277
00:14:24,420 --> 00:14:27,220
there was still a lot of foam in my beer glass, wasn't there?

278
00:14:27,220 --> 00:14:28,920
Or, are you insinuating

279
00:14:28,920 --> 00:14:32,420
that I used magic or something to make the beer foam?

280
00:14:32,420 --> 00:14:36,120
Abracadabra.

281
00:14:36,120 --> 00:14:40,120
How strange. There's so much foam.

282
00:14:43,520 --> 00:14:46,320
The foam should've been gone and yet why?

283
00:14:46,320 --> 00:14:50,120
I poured in the salt that I found in the kitchen of this room.

284
00:14:50,120 --> 00:14:53,420
If you pour salt into beer, will it foam up?

285
00:14:53,420 --> 00:14:55,820
If it's any type of grain that sinks in beer,

286
00:14:55,820 --> 00:14:58,620
I guess anything will do whether it's sugar, sand, and so on.

287
00:14:58,620 --> 00:15:00,820
The point is, when it sinks,

288
00:15:00,820 --> 00:15:03,920
and a lot of space is created between the air and beer,

289
00:15:03,920 --> 00:15:07,920
carbon dioxide seems to gather there, and create foams.

290
00:15:09,420 --> 00:15:10,420
So, see.

291
00:15:10,420 --> 00:15:12,520
In the other beer glasses where the foams have disappeared,

292
00:15:12,520 --> 00:15:14,520
if you pour salt into them...

293
00:15:17,620 --> 00:15:19,420
-True. -Wow.

294
00:15:19,420 --> 00:15:23,220
But, Conan, it's amazing that you knew something like this.

295
00:15:24,220 --> 00:15:26,920
Pops Kogoro told me about it once.

296
00:15:26,920 --> 00:15:29,020
How about it, surprised?

297
00:15:29,020 --> 00:15:30,720
When I was a poor student,

298
00:15:30,720 --> 00:15:33,220
I used to use this method a lot.

299
00:15:33,220 --> 00:15:35,320
When he was a university student he was poor,

300
00:15:35,320 --> 00:15:38,720
so he used to pour in salt occasionally so people wouldn't notice

301
00:15:38,720 --> 00:15:40,820
that he was sipping beer that lost all foam.

302
00:15:40,820 --> 00:15:42,120
By the way,

303
00:15:42,120 --> 00:15:47,120
it seems that this method is also used when taking pictures of beer.

304
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:51,320
Because it looks more delicious with foam.

305
00:15:51,320 --> 00:15:54,820
It's something that you, a cameraman would know about.

306
00:15:54,820 --> 00:15:58,620
But... I didn't have any salt on me back then.

307
00:15:58,620 --> 00:16:01,720
But, Mr. Ogino, when we came into the room

308
00:16:01,720 --> 00:16:05,720
you kicked the package that was at the entrance, didn't you?

309
00:16:11,620 --> 00:16:15,020
That was something you brought back from the funeral, right?

310
00:16:15,020 --> 00:16:18,020
If so, it would've been inside, no?

311
00:16:18,020 --> 00:16:20,020
The "cleansing salt".

312
00:16:21,420 --> 00:16:24,220
I see, so he used that salt.

313
00:16:24,220 --> 00:16:26,520
Yes, most likely.

314
00:16:26,520 --> 00:16:29,120
Because after he kicked it,

315
00:16:29,120 --> 00:16:30,920
he returned the tea package that fell out.

316
00:16:30,920 --> 00:16:34,620
Back then, he took out the "cleansing salt"

317
00:16:34,620 --> 00:16:36,020
and snuck it into his pocket.

318
00:16:36,020 --> 00:16:37,920
He then broke the packet open,

319
00:16:37,920 --> 00:16:39,720
picked up several grains of salt.

320
00:16:39,720 --> 00:16:43,820
Then, just before showing me the beer glass,

321
00:16:43,820 --> 00:16:47,320
poured salt into it and showed me the beer with foams.

322
00:16:47,320 --> 00:16:50,820
Well, it must've been a trick that he thought up

323
00:16:50,820 --> 00:16:54,620
at the spur of the moment.

324
00:16:54,620 --> 00:16:56,720
Even if he were to have disposed of the salt packet somewhere,

325
00:16:56,720 --> 00:16:59,720
there should be several grains of salt left in his pocket.

326
00:16:59,720 --> 00:17:03,020
Besides, if he did push someone off the veranda,

327
00:17:03,020 --> 00:17:05,720
they must've struggled slightly.

328
00:17:05,720 --> 00:17:07,620
And if you consider the fact that

329
00:17:07,620 --> 00:17:11,820
he had to rush out of the room as soon as possible,

330
00:17:11,820 --> 00:17:16,720
if we check the carpet that President Katsumoto had installed last night,

331
00:17:16,720 --> 00:17:18,420
I'm sure we'll still be able to find it, no?

332
00:17:19,820 --> 00:17:22,820
The trace of you having gone to the President's room

333
00:17:22,820 --> 00:17:26,220
between last night and this morning.

334
00:17:28,820 --> 00:17:32,820
But, it's hard to believe

335
00:17:32,820 --> 00:17:34,220
that Mr. Ogino would kill President Katsumoto.

336
00:17:34,220 --> 00:17:36,020
Right. Because even the lawyer told us

337
00:17:36,020 --> 00:17:39,520
that our chances of winning were good.

338
00:17:39,520 --> 00:17:42,720
In the first place, you said so too, Mr. Ogino.

339
00:17:42,720 --> 00:17:45,720
That on the memory card that had the successive pictures in it,

340
00:17:45,720 --> 00:17:48,120
the fingerprints of the president were on,

341
00:17:48,120 --> 00:17:49,320
so that it would prove that...

342
00:17:49,320 --> 00:17:52,120
the president had chosen the pictures in question,

343
00:17:52,120 --> 00:17:53,720
on his own and put them on the magazine.

344
00:17:55,220 --> 00:17:56,920
Why would he want to kill the president

345
00:17:56,920 --> 00:17:58,720
knowing that he would be winning the case?

346
00:17:58,720 --> 00:18:00,920
It disappeared.

347
00:18:00,920 --> 00:18:02,520
Disappeared?

348
00:18:02,520 --> 00:18:06,520
Since I received that strange mail this morning from the president,

349
00:18:06,520 --> 00:18:09,420
I had this uneasy feeling, so I checked...

350
00:18:09,420 --> 00:18:14,520
and found that the memory card had disappeared from my camera bag.

351
00:18:16,320 --> 00:18:19,520
I had an idea of who it was right away,

352
00:18:19,520 --> 00:18:22,020
so I went to the president's room

353
00:18:22,020 --> 00:18:23,720
and pressed him for an answer. Just as I thought...

354
00:18:23,720 --> 00:18:25,320
Cut it out.

355
00:18:25,320 --> 00:18:28,720
Why don't you ask your assistant who quit the other day

356
00:18:28,720 --> 00:18:30,020
about that memory card?

357
00:18:30,020 --> 00:18:32,220
Well, I'm sure he split somewhere abroad

358
00:18:32,220 --> 00:18:35,220
after making a lot of cash and is enjoying himself.

359
00:18:35,220 --> 00:18:38,020
I don't think you can contact him by phone either.

360
00:18:38,020 --> 00:18:39,620
Just as I thought...

361
00:18:39,620 --> 00:18:42,820
You paid him to steal that memory card.

362
00:18:43,920 --> 00:18:48,020
He told me that you guys were planning to place charges against me.

363
00:18:48,020 --> 00:18:50,420
Well, if you're not going to withdraw charges,

364
00:18:50,420 --> 00:18:52,720
I've got something in mind too.

365
00:18:52,720 --> 00:18:58,120
Those successive pictures will be used as a newly acquired scoop too.

366
00:18:59,120 --> 00:19:04,620
With the headline, "A Ruthless Cameraman who Sold his Classmate."

367
00:19:07,620 --> 00:19:08,920
Classmate?

368
00:19:08,920 --> 00:19:10,420
With that actress?

369
00:19:10,420 --> 00:19:13,720
Yes, we were classmates in intermediate school.

370
00:19:13,720 --> 00:19:17,120
That's why I knew that the guy who was with her

371
00:19:17,120 --> 00:19:19,820
was her younger step-brother.

372
00:19:19,820 --> 00:19:23,220
And I didn't take that picture without permission.

373
00:19:24,320 --> 00:19:28,620
I took it right in front of them so that I could send it to them.

374
00:19:28,620 --> 00:19:32,220
My assistant, mistook that picture

375
00:19:32,220 --> 00:19:33,720
and showed it to the president on his own

376
00:19:33,720 --> 00:19:35,520
and made up that darn article.

377
00:19:35,520 --> 00:19:39,820
That's why I couldn't forgive him

378
00:19:39,820 --> 00:19:44,020
when thinking that the picture that I took

379
00:19:44,020 --> 00:19:47,320
served as a factor in driving her to commit suicide.

380
00:19:47,320 --> 00:19:50,020
By the time I snapped back to myself,

381
00:19:50,020 --> 00:19:53,320
the president was lying flat on the ground like a frog.

382
00:19:55,720 --> 00:20:00,020
But, for a murder that wasn't planned ahead of time,

383
00:20:00,020 --> 00:20:03,920
I thought that the beer foam trick would get me through.

384
00:20:03,920 --> 00:20:06,420
To think that the trick actually lead to me being suspected

385
00:20:06,420 --> 00:20:08,720
and even served as proof against me...

386
00:20:11,220 --> 00:20:13,620
I suspected you as being the culprit

387
00:20:13,620 --> 00:20:16,520
ever since I heard that you were a cameraman.

388
00:20:16,520 --> 00:20:17,720
No joke.

389
00:20:17,720 --> 00:20:21,220
Because when you got to the site,

390
00:20:21,220 --> 00:20:25,020
all you had on you was your cell phone and nothing else.

391
00:20:25,020 --> 00:20:28,720
That's why I had my eye on you from the start.

392
00:20:28,720 --> 00:20:31,520
But, if he heard the commotion and came,

393
00:20:31,520 --> 00:20:32,920
having nothing on him would be natural.

394
00:20:32,920 --> 00:20:34,320
No.

395
00:20:34,320 --> 00:20:41,320
A press cameraman would never forget the camera

396
00:20:41,320 --> 00:20:43,920
that brings in the bread.

397
00:22:08,320 --> 00:22:11,020
Well, how amazing, Officer Takagi!

398
00:22:11,020 --> 00:22:13,020
You're pretty good when you want to be.

399
00:22:13,020 --> 00:22:14,820
Right.

400
00:22:14,820 --> 00:22:17,820
Oh, well, not really...

401
00:22:17,820 --> 00:22:21,720
All I did was talk as was written in Shinichi's mail though.

402
00:22:23,820 --> 00:22:26,920
It seems that the case has been solved...

403
00:23:16,820 --> 00:23:19,620
From here, it's my area.

404
00:23:19,620 --> 00:23:21,620
It's not where you come in.

405
00:23:24,720 --> 00:23:28,220
Adults get cold easily and don't like the cold.

406
00:23:28,220 --> 00:23:30,020
What's the matter? Both of you...

407
00:23:31,420 --> 00:23:32,920
The door's left opened.

408
00:23:32,920 --> 00:23:34,120
It's nothing.

409
00:23:34,120 --> 00:23:35,120
Let's go home.

410
00:23:35,120 --> 00:23:36,520
Let's go.

411
00:23:36,520 --> 00:23:38,820
It's getting a bit chilly.

412
00:23:53,820 --> 00:23:56,720
Wait, Candy!

413
00:23:56,720 --> 00:23:59,820
Kingo Ebisawa and Ginji Kaniyama,

414
00:23:59,820 --> 00:24:02,320
both have previous police records of committing robbery.

415
00:24:04,020 --> 00:24:05,320
What's with you?

416
00:24:05,320 --> 00:24:08,020
What's going to happen to Candy?

417
00:24:08,020 --> 00:24:10,020
Inspector, if I remember correctly,

418
00:24:10,020 --> 00:24:13,620
you said that the two were listening to police radio communication?

419
00:24:13,620 --> 00:24:16,220
If... if we go that way, we'll run into the next checkpoint.

420
00:24:16,220 --> 00:24:18,020
Where are you?

421
00:24:18,020 --> 00:24:19,720
Next Conan,

422
00:24:19,720 --> 00:24:23,620
"The Car Carrying a Time-Bomb".

423
00:24:47,220 --> 00:24:48,520
No, I think you are.

